<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-06-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-06-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="964" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d964">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/15959</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-13">June 13, 1940</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>In view of this apparently indiscriminate bombing of Chungking
                                without reference to military objectives, should we call it to the
                                attention of the Japanese Government?</p>
                            <closer><signed>F[<hi rend="smallcaps">ranklin</hi>] D. R[<hi rend="smallcaps">oosevelt</hi>]</signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>